The concept of niche breadth can be applied to comparative studies of diet between populations or species (Slatyer, Hirst & Sexton, 2013), even if it has not always been treated within this contextual vocabulary (e.g., Rehage, Barnett & Sih, 2005; Luiselli et al., 2007; Dalpadado & Mowbray, 2013). We calculated niche breadth for all populations using the evenness measure J’. This index is based on the Shannon–Wiener’s index H’ (Shannon & Weaver, 1964), as recommended by Colwell & Futuyma (1971): \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
